topic.title: Route-To-Self Command

body.p: The Route-To-Self Command configures a port to take arriving TLPs at the ingress of the port and routes it to itself. Using RTS can potentially create loops so care must be taken when using this feature. The RTS feature can be configured to route to self for TLPs with one of the following characteristics:
1. Going upstream from Endpoint with target address in its own address range.
2. Going downstream through Switch USP with target address (prefetchable and non-prefetchable) less than or greater than the address range owned by Switch USP.

The sub command codes:
0x0 - Route-To-Self Set
0x1 - Route-To-Self Get

topic.title: Route-To-Self — Set Sub-Command

section.p: The Route-To-Self Set sub-command is used to configure the routing method of MMIO TLP whose target address is:
1. Within the address range of its originator when going upstream from Endpoint.
2. Beyond the address range owned by Switch USP when going downstream through Switch USP.
The ID of the partition to which the logical bridge binding instance belongs. Valid values are '0' to 'number of partitions - 1'
The ID of the logical bridge instance to which the physical port will be bound. ID '0' is always the ID of the USP. Valid values are from '1' to 'number of DSP'.
0x1: Route-To-Self TLP will be routed back to its originator.
There is no output data for this sub-command.

topic.title: Route-To-Self — Get Sub-Command

section.p: The Route-To-Self Get sub-command is used to get the Route-To-Self setting information.
The ID of the partition to which the logical bridge binding instance belongs. Valid values are '0' to 'number of partitions - 1'
The ID of the logical bridge binding instance to which the physical port will be bound. ID '0' is always the ID of the USP. Valid values are from '1' to 'number of DSP.
0x01: Route-To-Self TLP will be routed back to its originator.
